place.name: SOUTH CREAKE
place.gazetteerText: CREAKE (South), a parish in Docking district, Norfolk; 3½ miles SSE of Burnham-Westgate r. station, and 5¼ W by S of Walsingham. It has a post office under Fakenham. Acres, 4, 146. Real property, £6, 185. Pop., 1, 058. Houses, 213. The property is much sub-divided. There are a Saxon camp and numerous tumuli. The living is a vicarage in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £440.* Patron, the Marquis Townshend. The church has a fine font, and is good; and there are an Independent chapel, a national school, and charities £38. Bishop Pearson was a native. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
